      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Dravula</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Well from personal experience I died so damn many times from levels 1 to 3 it's not funny. It's very easy to give up at this point. You get so easily swarmed by spiders and crap in Nektulos around the newbie log. </P><P>12th level is that first early level where you realize how potent this class is. You get Heatblood, Engulfing Darkness, Leach and Lifedraw for some serious ass kicking. You can take mobs no other class can at that level.</P><P>The next nice level is 24 where you pet turns that mean looking dark brown color :) You also get shock of poison. At 29 you get the dual wielding pet and finally a new dot in Boilblood -- a, mean nasty one too. I make it clear to others that when I'm casting this spell it's doing 500pts damage with my hotkey -- "Dotting %T with Boil Blood, a 500pt dot" so they have an idea of what kind of damage I'm doing and not just sitting around on my ass and sending in the pet when a pull comes in :)</P><P>So now I'm one bub away from 34 and dying to get the new pet, VoSS, root(yea finally!) and Torbas'. Quite literally dying I might add. I've been so careless lately that I died 4 times in OT today. Luckily I got 50% xp rezz on each one. Can't wait for 34 and then losing that damn spell book at 35. Then the new nasty pet with 50% haste buff at 39 then... oh well you get the idea :)</P><P>Defintely group as much as possible too. People are always amazed when I tell them what a necro can do. We have our nasty dots and pets but also heals, buffs, mana transfers, mezzing, nukes, and of course snaring and fearing that can add so much to a group.</P><P>You'l have fun. Just be prepared to die a lot in the early levels.</P><P><b>Dravula</b> 33rd DE Necro</P><P>Edited by - Dravula on 05/08/2001  03:44:35</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Abillister</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>First off i have to tell Dravula that boil only does 400...27dmg * 15 rounds</P><P>Soloing can be better, but with the new dungeon, grouping bonus, and velious mobs grouping is becoming more needed.  But you don't need to, which is always nice.  You can do high damage, with low mana cost...and if you sit and med while mob is feared you will end battle with around 80% mana, which unless you can get one of those great groups with a good puller, you'll be able to get more exp this way.  at 40 (solo) i can do about 2.2k damage in about 90 seconds (not counting pet), and (assuming no resists) still have around 2 bubs of mana.  </P><P>Personally I try and get all caster groups if i can, nothing like 3 mages, a necro, a chanter, and a druid (for pulling and buffs).  The pets do massive damage but since none of them do 1/2 they take less exp then 1 tank would.  You have druid snare pull, you fear, send pets, all the mages drop about 1-2 spells (and depending on your lvl you can drop a DD or 2) and mob dead.  Everyone ends battle with around 80% mana, pets are still basically full HP, so you can keep a constant pull going.  </P><P>The only time you ever really need a group though is dungeons, even with root/mez it is still a pain to hunt in dungeons unless you are about 10 lvls higher...and even then it can be annoying.  Also, even if you want to solo all the way to 55, please group now and then...i've gone into several zones and said "lvl __ necro lfg" and immediatly gotten a tell (even in dungeons) because people have seen that we can do just about anything needed...root, mez, pet, high dmg fast DoT's (VoS for example), and if needed you can drop ench or cleric a quick twitch.</P><P></P><P><marquee><b><font=red> ABILLISTER "MONKEY" ABU-Povar</font></b></marquee><BR><marquee><a href="<a href="http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp" target="_blank">http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp</a>" target="_New">Sojourn's Talon</a></marquee></font></td>
